org.xflatdb.xflat

Class DatabaseConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xflatdb.xflat.DatabaseConfig

  • public class DatabaseConfig
extends java.lang.Object
    The Configuration for a new XFlat Database.
    This Configuration must be passed to the XFlatDatabase.setConfig(org.xflatdb.xflat.DatabaseConfig) method before initialization, or the default values will be used.

    This class is immutable, all set methods return new objects.

      • getIdGeneratorStrategy

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Class<? extends IdGenerator>> getIdGeneratorStrategy()
        Gets the ID generator strategy used by this Database.

        ID generators are selected on a per-table basis by the Database based on an ID generation strategy. The strategy selects the first IdGenerator in the list that supports the ID property's type.

        Returns:
        An unmodifiable list of the ID generators in the strategy.

      • getThreadCount

        public int getThreadCount()
        Gets the number of threads that this Database will spool up in its executor service.

        This is unused if an executor service is provided to the Database upon construction.

        Returns:
        the size of the database's thread pool
        See Also:
        withThreadCount(int)

      • getPojoConverterClass

        public java.lang.String getPojoConverterClass()
        Gets the binary name of the class used by the database to automatically map and convert POJOs to XML for the database. This class must implement PojoConverter.

        The database will load this class using its ClassLoader in order to convert pojos.

        Returns:
        The binary name of the class which will be loaded in order to automatically map POJOs for conversion to XML.

      • withIdGeneratorStrategy

        public DatabaseConfig withIdGeneratorStrategy(java.util.List<java.lang.Class<? extends IdGenerator>> strategy)
        Sets the ID generator strategy used by this Database.

        ID generators are selected on a per-table basis by the Database based on an ID generation strategy. The strategy selects the first IdGenerator in the list that supports the ID property's type.

        Parameters:
        strategy - The strategy to use for this database.
        Returns:
        A new instance of the DatabaseConfig using this strategy.

      • withThreadCount

        public DatabaseConfig withThreadCount(int threadCount)
        Sets the number of threads that this Database will spool up in its executor service.

        The database uses an ExecutorService to manage scheduled and recurring tasks. This sets the size of its thread pool.
        This is unused if an executor service is provided to the Database upon construction.

        Parameters:
        threadCount - The number of threads in the database's thread pool.
        Returns:
        A new instance with the ThreadCount property set.

      • setPojoConverterClass

        public DatabaseConfig setPojoConverterClass(java.lang.String className)
        Sets the binary name of the class used by the database to convert POJOs for the database. The class MUST be an implementation of PojoConverter. This class is only loaded when needed, in order to avoid requiring JARs that are unnecessary. The default value is a JAXB-based implementation. If the PojoConverter is never used, the JAXB context will never be loaded, and the JAXB jars will not be necessary on the classpath.
        Parameters:
        className -
        Returns:
        A new instance with the pojoConverterClass property set.

        Parameters:
        tableConfig - The default table config to use.
        Returns:
        A new instance with the defaultTableConfig property set.
